In article <TK.92Mar7162201@wheat-chex.ai.mit.edu> tk@ai.mit.edu (Tom Knight) writes:
>I read in the paper (Boston Globe) today that the FCC wants to require
>all broadcast and fiber carriers to insert wiretapping mechanisms into
>their hardware/software to comply with government subpoenas.  

Does this proposed reg cover enhanced service providers too?  We
sell e-mail feeds, I'd hate to have to install wiretapping equipment
so that the feds can read e-mail going through the system (not
too good for business....)

Sounds a lot like the crypto back door that got squashed a few months
ago.
